18:51.496 --> 18:54.965
Oh... I never felt
               like this before!

18:55.033 --> 18:57.234
My legs are like
                      jelly, oh!

18:57.301 --> 19:00.337
You make me feel
             like a little girl!

19:00.405 --> 19:02.406
You make me feel
                   like a woman!

19:02.473 --> 19:04.908
You make me feel
            like a flying horse!

19:04.976 --> 19:07.911
What do you want?!
              What do you want?!

19:07.979 --> 19:09.680
Sanity. Sanity.

19:09.748 --> 19:11.649
Just one moment
of sanity, that's all.

19:11.716 --> 19:13.917
Sanity.

19:18.222 --> 19:22.859
Alex... please,

19:22.927 --> 19:25.495
you have to help me.

19:25.563 --> 19:31.234
Otherwise, Latka and I will
 really have to get a divorce.

19:31.302 --> 19:33.971
Simka, I am <i>not</i> going
      to make love to you.

19:50.221 --> 19:51.721
I'm sorry.

19:54.459 --> 19:56.360
I'm gonna take you home.

20:03.468 --> 20:07.071
Listen, it's, uh...
it's cold.

20:07.138 --> 20:09.273
Better button up.

20:14.646 --> 20:16.513
Okay.

20:28.993 --> 20:31.228
Oh, I'm glad
               to see you, Alex.

20:31.296 --> 20:35.965
I stayed with Latka
        because apparently he...

20:36.033 --> 20:37.167
he has some trouble,

20:37.235 --> 20:42.339
and I only wish
I could follow it.

20:42.407 --> 20:43.807
It seems...

20:43.875 --> 20:46.743
No, Jim, Jim, Jim,
           don't worry about it.

20:46.810 --> 20:48.145
Everything is
                  all right now.

20:48.213 --> 20:50.480
Alex, Simka and I are
           both grateful to you.

20:50.548 --> 20:52.248
Now get out of my
               sight, you swine.

20:55.920 --> 20:59.689
I have bad news
      for you, my darling.

20:59.757 --> 21:02.492
I have been
        faithful to you.

21:02.560 --> 21:06.129
Oh, no!

21:06.197 --> 21:12.002
Now this is where
        I get confused.

21:12.070 --> 21:13.770
If I can get over this part,

21:13.838 --> 21:15.572
I know I can help him.

21:15.640 --> 21:17.107
Yeah, Jim, just hold it.

21:20.845 --> 21:23.714
So we must part now forever,
          my beloved.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.715
Latka! Latka, you're not going

21:25.783 --> 21:27.618
to go through with this,
            are you?

21:27.686 --> 21:31.721
Alex, we must.
      It is the only way.

21:31.789 --> 21:34.992
Are you ready
         to complete the circle?

21:35.060 --> 21:39.863
I must take one last look
       at you as my wife.

21:39.931 --> 21:44.168
Simka,
 you will always have my heart.

21:44.235 --> 21:46.102
I don't need it without you.

21:48.806 --> 21:50.407
I will miss you.

21:50.474 --> 21:54.678
I will miss your touch.

21:54.746 --> 22:00.851
I will miss the children
     we could have had together.

22:00.919 --> 22:02.919
Good-bye, Latka.

22:35.319 --> 22:37.621
Are they unhappy...

22:39.858 --> 22:41.792
...b-because
they got divorced?

22:41.860 --> 22:43.793
Yeah.

22:44.996 --> 22:47.897
Why don't they just
get married again?

22:47.965 --> 22:49.899
It's not that
                    simple, Jim.

22:49.967 --> 22:51.902
You think they'd go
       through this kind of hell

22:51.969 --> 22:54.037
if they could
               just marry again?

22:59.543 --> 23:02.545
We must seek the
      Reverend Gorky right away!

23:02.613 --> 23:04.380
Jim, thank you!

23:04.448 --> 23:05.716
Mwa!

23:05.784 --> 23:07.885
Thank you very much.

23:07.952 --> 23:10.386
Let's try to make it work
this time.

23:17.761 --> 23:19.329
Piece of cake.

